dany (1.9.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Internationalized domain name (IDN) support: hostnames are now normalized
    to their IDNA A-label (punycode) form at query intake, so a UTF-8 name
    (dany münchen.de) resolves identically to its already-encoded equivalent
    (dany xn--mnchen-3ya.de). Names are case-folded and NFC-normalized in the
    process; underscore labels (_dmarc.<domain>, --usd probes) are preserved.
    This applies to both dany and dnx, and to the library — RunQuery and
    RunNXQuery normalize Query.Hostname before dialing, leaving the caller's
    *Query unmutated and emitting Answers tagged with the A-label form.

  * A hostname that IDNA rejects is now surfaced as a *QueryError carrying the
    new stable Code "INVALID_NAME"; RunQuery fires no lookups for it. RunNXQuery
    has no error channel, so it falls back to a best-effort lookup of the
    original name (which reads as not-NX, matching the existing bias).

  * golang.org/x/net is now a direct dependency (for golang.org/x/net/idna).

 -- Gavin Carr <gavin@openfusion.net>  Mon, 13 Jul 2026 15:50:00 +0800

dany (1.8.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Library fix: RunQuery/RunNXQuery now honour Query.Resolvers. Previously
    they dialled Query.Server only and never consulted Resolvers, so a
    library caller that set Resolvers alone — exactly as the README example
    shows — dialled the empty string and got a "missing address" error for
    every type. The Resolvers→server bridge (round-robin pick + default DNS
    port) is now done inside the library; an explicit Server still wins, so
    the CLIs are unchanged.

  * Concurrency fixes surfaced by library use:
    - Error suppression is now a per-lookup argument. RunQuery used to flip
      the shared Query.IgnoreErrors true for the best-effort USD/www probes;
      the apex-type goroutines read the same field, so the write both raced
      with their reads and leaked suppression onto the apex queries —
      silently swallowing real SERVFAIL/REFUSED rcodes. Apex errors now
      surface again while USD/www stay best-effort.
    - Resolvers.Next() is now concurrency-safe. Its Index read-modify-write
      was unlocked, yet dnx (and now RunQuery) call it from concurrent
      goroutines on a shared *Resolvers; under -race this raced and could
      panic with an out-of-range index. It is now mutex-guarded, with the
      single-resolver fast path kept lock-free.

 -- Gavin Carr <gavin@openfusion.net>  Fri, 10 Jul 2026 15:44:29 +0800

dany (1.7.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Library ergonomics: NewResolvers is now variadic, so a round-robin
    resolver set can be built in a single call — NewResolvers(ip1, ip2, ...)
    or NewResolvers(slice...) — instead of seeding with one IP and
    Append()ing the rest. The single-IP form is unchanged. It now panics if
    called with no IPs, since an empty set has no resolver for Next() to
    return.

  * New NewResolversFromStrings([]string) (*Resolvers, error) helper: parses
    and validates a list of IP-address strings, returning an error on the
    first unparseable entry rather than the silent nil that net.ParseIP
    yields. LoadResolvers now reuses it, removing a duplicated parse loop; a
    latent unclosed-file-handle leak in LoadResolvers is fixed at the same
    time.

  * Docs: the README now documents the dnx CLI and using dany as a library,
    and the stale default-types list is corrected to include HTTPS.

 -- Gavin Carr <gavin@openfusion.net>  Fri, 10 Jul 2026 11:48:03 +0800

dany (1.6.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * HTTPS/SVCB record support (RFC 9460): dany now queries the modern
    service-binding records. HTTPS (type 65) is in the default set, since it
    lives at the bare hostname browsers query for every https:// connection;
    SVCB (type 64), the generic prefix-anchored form, is included under
    --all. SvcParams render non-opaquely — space-joined key=value pairs in
    text, and an ordered params list in -f json/yaml.

  * Extended --usd probes: added TLSRPT (_smtp._tls), BIMI (default._bimi),
    and atproto (_atproto, Bluesky handle identity) to the well-known
    underscore-label set, alongside the existing DMARC/DKIM/MTA-STS probes.

  * DNSSEC records, triaged by usefulness: --all now shows the DNSKEY + DS
    chain-of-trust summary (DS, the parent-side trust link, was previously
    absent). A new --dnssec flag adds the DNSSEC set (DNSKEY,DS,NSEC); the
    opaque, constantly-re-signed RRSIG is excluded from the bundle because a
    bare RRSIG query almost always SERVFAILs on recursive resolvers, but it
    remains reachable via an explicit -t RRSIG.

  * Bug fix: both CLIs migrated off the stdlib log package to slog. Because
    slog.SetDefault also reroutes stdlib log at Info level while the default
    handler level is Warn, fatal errors (invalid -t type, bad --server,
    missing resolver file) were silently swallowed — the process exited
    non-zero with no message. Fatal paths now use slog.Error, so the error
    is always printed.

 -- Gavin Carr <gavin@openfusion.net>  Thu, 09 Jul 2026 13:23:10 +0800

dany (1.5.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Structured-output deduplication: `-f json`/`-f yaml` now deduplicate
    answers on RRset identity (type, name, class, rdata), keeping the lowest
    TTL, so genuine wire-duplicate resource records (the same RR returned
    twice in one response — which occurs in the wild) collapse to a single
    entry rather than appearing twice. This brings structured output in line
    with the text renderer, which already deduplicated, and with RFC 2181 §5
    (an RRset is a set). Name-distinct records are preserved: www/apex
    address pairs, per-IP PTRs, and CNAME chain hops keep their separate
    entries. A related effect: when several query types traverse the same
    CNAME (e.g. `-t A,AAAA` against an aliased host), the shared CNAME hop is
    now recorded once instead of once per type. The output envelope shape is
    unchanged (schema_version stays 1).

 -- Gavin Carr <gavin@openfusion.net>  Thu, 09 Jul 2026 11:39:41 +0800

dany (1.4.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * USD empty-non-terminal reporting: `--usd` probes now surface a name that
    exists but returns no records (NOERROR/NODATA — a DNS empty non-terminal)
    as a "present; no records" answer. The motivating case is
    `_domainkey.<domain>`: a bare query never returns a DKIM key (keys live
    under non-enumerable `<selector>._domainkey` names), but NODATA versus
    NXDOMAIN distinguishes "DKIM is deployed" from "no DKIM at all" — signal
    that was previously discarded. NXDOMAIN stays omitted, and ordinary
    NODATA on non-USD queries is unchanged.

  * Text output renders the marker as `[present; no records]`, tag-aware:
    the owner name appears in the value when untagged, or in the tag column
    under `--tag`. JSON and YAML gain an additive `present_empty: true`
    discriminator on the answer (no schema-version bump); existing
    record-bearing output is unchanged.

 -- Gavin Carr <gavin@openfusion.net>  Thu, 09 Jul 2026 10:48:13 +0800

dany (1.3.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Structured output ordering: JSON and YAML answers and errors are now
    sorted into a stable total order (by type, then rdata, name, TTL), so
    consecutive `-f json`/`-f yaml` runs are byte-comparable. Previously the
    concurrent query fan-out left records in nondeterministic arrival order.
    Text output ordering is unchanged.

  * Natural numeric sorting: numeric rdata fields now sort by value rather
    than lexically across all output formats, so MX preferences order
    9 < 10 < 20 < 100 (not 10 < 100 < 20 < 9) and A records order
    10.0.0.2 < 10.0.0.10. Applies to both the text renderer and the
    JSON/YAML envelope.

  * CNAME chain capture: JSON and YAML now record each CNAME hop traversed
    while resolving a query (owner name in `name`, target in `rdata` and
    `data.target`), so the full alias chain is reconstructable — the mapping
    was previously discarded after being followed. Text output is unchanged
    (the resolved target records are shown as before), and explicit
    `-t CNAME` queries are unaffected.

 -- Gavin Carr <gavin@openfusion.net>  Wed, 08 Jul 2026 13:31:19 +0800

dany (1.2.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Flag parsing: both CLIs migrate from jessevdk/go-flags to
    alecthomas/kong, bringing the project in line with the standard Go
    CLI stack. --help output structure now follows kong's conventions
    (Arguments / Flags sections, =STRING placeholders); the runtime
    "Default/Supported types" footer is preserved via a kong.Help hook
    in both CLIs. dany still accepts its two deprecated positional-arg
    forms (@<ip> server, bare <RR>[,<RR>...] types list) with the same
    runtime deprecation warning as before.

  * Coloured --help: integrated github.com/gavincarr/kong-help-colours
    so --help emits yellow section headers, green flag tokens, and cyan
    placeholders when stdout is a TTY and NO_COLOR is unset. Falls back
    to the default plain printer otherwise, so piped/non-TTY help output
    is byte-identical.

 -- Gavin Carr <gavin@openfusion.net>  Wed, 27 May 2026 12:21:28 +0800

dany (1.1.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Logging: both CLIs switch from a bespoke vprintf/verbose-bool to
    log/slog with github.com/lmittmann/tint, matching the standard Go
    CLI stack. -v now counts: bare -v enables Info, -vv enables Debug;
    default level is Warn so nothing is printed without -v. dnx's
    per-hostname "looking up" line drops to Debug so bulk stdin runs
    aren't flooded with one info line per host.

  * Testability: extracted runCLI(opts, io.Writer) from both main()
    functions. opts/parser are no longer package-level state, errors
    propagate as return values instead of log.Fatal mid-flow, and the
    renderer writes through a caller-supplied io.Writer so end-to-end
    tests capture output into a bytes.Buffer rather than exec'ing the
    binary. Five new offline end-to-end tests cover dany text/JSON
    rendering + -o override and dnx NXDOMAIN/Count modes.

  * Packaging: new scripts/deb_tarball.sh wraps the local source tree
    into dist/deb/dany_<version>.tar.gz — stripped static binaries +
    debian/ + LICENCE + README, ready for `dpkg-buildpackage -b` on a
    build machine. Version is read from debian/changelog via
    dpkg-parsechangelog (same single source of truth as
    scripts/release.sh), and a fresh CGO_ENABLED=0 / -buildvcs=false
    build is forced so the static-binary guarantees are applied.

 -- Gavin Carr <gavin@openfusion.net>  Mon, 25 May 2026 15:53:21 +0800

dany (1.0.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * New flag: -w/--www. Probes the www.<hostname> label in addition to
    the apex. Defaults to A+AAAA, but honors an explicit -t/--types or
    -a/--all (so `dany -w -t mx` queries MX against www. too). In
    tagged mode (-T), apex and www results are emitted on separate
    hostname-tagged lines; in untagged mode they share the output and
    identical rows are deduped, so a www that resolves to the apex IP
    doesn't appear twice. Render also dedups identical lines
    unconditionally now — only observable when -w introduces duplicates.

  * New flag: -f/--fmt {text,json,yaml,yml}. Adds structured output
    alongside the default tab-separated text. Each record carries both
    `rdata` (DNS presentation form) and a typed `data` payload — e.g.
    `{preference, exchange}` for MX, full RFC field set for SOA,
    `{strings: [...]}` for TXT. A versioned envelope (schema_version: 1)
    wraps the per-hostname output; multi-host runs emit NDJSON (json
    mode) or multi-document YAML (yaml mode, `---`-separated). In
    structured modes, errors fold into the envelope's `errors` field
    with a stable machine-readable `code` (NXDOMAIN, SERVFAIL,
    EXCHANGE_ERROR, UNSUPPORTED_TYPE) — nothing goes to stderr. PTR
    records (with -p/--ptr) appear as standalone entries with the
    source IP carried in `data.ip` for easy joining (text mode folds
    them into the matching A/AAAA row as before). `yml` is a
    convenience alias for `yaml`.

  * New flag: --version on both `dany` and `dnx`. Long-only (`dnx`
    already uses -V for --invert); short-circuits print `<name>
    <version>` and exits before any other validation, so it works
    without other required arguments.

  * Library: errors from RunQuery / RunNXQuery are now *QueryError
    (Type, Hostname, Code, Err) instead of fmt.Errorf-wrapped strings.
    Error() preserves the historical message format and Unwrap exposes
    the underlying sentinel so errors.Is(err, ErrNXDomain/ErrServFail)
    continues to work for existing consumers.

  * Build: scripts/build_all.sh now exports CGO_ENABLED=0 so the
    resulting binaries are unconditionally pure-Go static (no libc /
    NSS resolver linkage), matching the Debian package description.
    Also passes -buildvcs=false so VCS metadata isn't baked in and
    commit-to-commit builds stay byte-stable.

  * Release flow: internal/version/VERSION is the single source of
    truth for the version string, //go:embed'd into both binaries.
    `scripts/release.sh <version>` syncs it with debian/changelog,
    commits, and annotated-tags; the changelog is the structural gate
    (no stanza, no release).

 -- Gavin Carr <gavin@openfusion.net>  Mon, 25 May 2026 13:20:47 +0800

dany (0.1.0) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial Debian packaging.
  * Ships two binaries: `dany` (DNS lookup tool that simulates ANY queries
    by firing typed RR lookups concurrently and aggregating results, with
    text/JSON/YAML output formats) and `dnx` (concurrent NXDOMAIN bulk
    prober for hostname lists).

